# Content & SEO Standards

## Source of Truth

HTML files in `content/tools/` are the source of truth for WordPress pages.
- File format: `.html` with YAML frontmatter
- Template: `content/tools/_template.html`

## Before Creating Any New Page

Answer these questions. If you can't, DO NOT create the page.

1. **What specific query is someone typing to find this?**
   - Must be a real search query, not marketing-speak
   - "openai 429 error fix" (good) vs "API Excellence Guide" (bad)

2. **What makes this page better than top 3 Google results?**
   - If you can't articulate this, don't create the page

3. **Would this cannibalize an existing page?**
   - If >50% overlap with existing page, expand that page instead

## Content Requirements

### Minimum Standards

| Page Type | Min Lines | Required Elements |
|-----------|-----------|-------------------|
| Tool page | 100+ | Widget, How to Use (3 steps), FAQ (5+), Related Tools (3-5) |
| Guide page | 200+ | Code examples (2+), troubleshooting steps, FAQ (5+) |
| Comparison | 150+ | Comparison table, "when to choose X" sections |

### Required Sections

1. **Title (H1)** — Must target the primary search query
2. **Intro paragraph** — 2-3 sentences explaining the problem
3. **Widget embed** — If applicable
4. **Substantive body content** — NOT just template boilerplate
5. **FAQ section** — Minimum 5 questions, including "Is this tool free?"
6. **Related Tools** — 3-5 internal links

### What "Substantive" Means

At least ONE of:
- Working code examples (Python, Node.js, etc.)
- Comparison tables with real numbers
- Step-by-step troubleshooting guides
- Common mistakes and how to avoid them

Template sections alone do NOT make a page valuable.

## SEO Technical Requirements

- `seo_title`: Under 60 characters, includes primary keyword
- `seo_description`: Under 155 characters, includes value proposition
- H1 must closely match the primary search query
- Slug format: `ai-{descriptive-slug}`

### Internal Linking

- Every page links OUT to 3-5 related tools/guides
- Every NEW page must be linked FROM at least 2 existing pages
- Use descriptive anchor text (not "click here")

## WordPress Workflow

### Push Commands

```bash
# Single page
python scripts/wp_pages.py push --file content/tools/{slug}.html

# All pages
python scripts/wp_pages.py push-all
```

### After Pushing: Verify with MCP Browser

1. Navigate to the page:
```
CallMcpTool: cursor-browser-extension / browser_navigate
Arguments: {"url": "https://www.ai-buzz.com/{slug}"}
```

2. Take a snapshot to verify:
```
CallMcpTool: cursor-browser-extension / browser_snapshot
```

3. Check for:
   - Page title matches expected
   - Tables render properly (not raw markdown)
   - Code blocks have proper formatting
   - Widget embeds load
   - Links work

### Content Template Structure

Frontmatter (YAML):
- `title` - Page title
- `slug` - URL slug (e.g., `ai-pricing-calculator`)
- `status` - `publish` or `draft`
- `seo_title` - AIOSEO title (under 60 chars)
- `seo_description` - Meta description (under 155 chars)
- `widget_endpoint` - API path for widget

### Widget Embedding

In WordPress/Bricks, use:

```html
<script
  src="https://ai-buzz-tools.onrender.com/embed.js"
  data-tool="error-decoder"
></script>
```

Tool names: `pricing`, `status`, `error-decoder`

## Site Structure

### Content Types

- **Tool Pages** (WordPress Pages): `/ai-pricing-calculator`, `/ai-status`, `/ai-error-decoder`, `/ai-tools` (hub)
- **Guide Posts** (WordPress Posts): Category "AI Developer Tools", e.g., `/ai-openai-429-errors`
- **Category Archive**: `/ai-developer-tools/` - lists all guide posts

### CLI Quick Reference

```bash
# Pages (tools)
python scripts/wp_pages.py push --file content/tools/ai-*.html
python scripts/wp_pages.py push-all

# Posts (guides)
python scripts/wp_pages.py push-post --file content/tools/ai-*.html
python scripts/wp_pages.py push-guides

# Other commands
python scripts/wp_pages.py list
python scripts/wp_pages.py pull --slug ai-pricing-calculator
python scripts/wp_pages.py diff --slug ai-pricing-calculator
```

### Troubleshooting

- **Widget not loading**: Check `data-tool` attribute matches valid tool name (`pricing`, `status`, `error-decoder`)
- **Page not found**: Verify slug with `wp_pages.py list`
- **WordPress not configured**: Check `.env` has `WORDPRESS_SITE_URL`, `WORDPRESS_USERNAME`, `WORDPRESS_APP_PASSWORD`

## Quality Checklist

Before pushing any content:

- [ ] Search query identified
- [ ] Meets minimum line count
- [ ] Has substantive content (code, tables, or guidance)
- [ ] No duplication with existing pages
- [ ] SEO meta complete (<60 title, <155 description)
- [ ] Links to 3-5 related pages
- [ ] FAQ has 5+ questions including "Is this free?"

**If any checkbox fails, do not publish.**

